ratings.question_text: What is your overall assessment of this course?

narratives.question_text: How would you summarize AFAM 505 01/AMST 643 01 for a fellow student? Would you recommend AFAM 505 01/AMST 643 01 to another student? Why or why not?
comments: The course covers some very interesting topics that bridge economics and computer science. I would recommend it for computer science students who already had some familiarity with concepts like Nash equilibrium, or for economics students who already were familiar with things like graph theory.
Using game theory to solve computer science problems

narratives.question_text: How did this course deepen your knowledge of your discipline/profession? To what extent did this course contribute to your dissertation/research?
comments: This course broadened my knowledge of topics in computer science, and their interactions with economics.
It would help to have a better understanding of how people in other fields look at game theory and instead of proving just existence of an equilibrium, some people really try find and implement one.
